---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is Haystack and what is it used for?",
    answer: "Haystack is an open-source NLP framework by deepset for building production-ready RAG and NLP pipelines. It uses a component-based architecture where you compose pipelines from modular, reusable Components (DocumentStore, Retriever, Reader, Embedder, LLM). Haystack is particularly strong for enterprise search, question answering systems, and RAG pipelines that need robust document preprocessing, multiple retrieval strategies, and production deployment."
  },
  {
    question: "What changed in Haystack 2.x?",
    answer: "Haystack 2.x (released 2024) was a major rewrite with a fundamentally new design. The old YAML-based pipeline definition and Node/Graph architecture was replaced with a Python-first, decorator-based Component system. Pipelines are now defined by connecting component inputs to outputs explicitly. The new design is more flexible, easier to debug, supports async execution, and works better with modern LLMs and RAG patterns."
  },
  {
    question: "What DocumentStore integrations does Haystack support?",
    answer: "Haystack integrates with most major document and vector stores: InMemoryDocumentStore (development/testing), Elasticsearch/OpenSearch (keyword + BM25), OpenSearch, FAISS (local vector search), Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, Chroma, and MongoDB Atlas Vector Search. Each DocumentStore can be swapped without changing the pipeline logic — a key advantage for testing vs. production configurations."
  },
  {
    question: "How does Haystack handle hybrid retrieval?",
    answer: "Haystack supports hybrid retrieval by running both a BM25 (sparse) retriever and an embedding (dense) retriever in the same pipeline, then merging results with a DocumentJoiner component using reciprocal rank fusion or score normalization. This is a native first-class pattern in Haystack — you declare two parallel retrieval branches and connect both to the joiner before the LLM step."
  },
  {
    question: "What is Deepset Cloud?",
    answer: "Deepset Cloud (now deepset AI Platform) is the managed enterprise platform built on top of Haystack. It provides a visual pipeline editor, hosted document stores, REST API deployment, fine-tuning, evaluation workflows, and access controls. It targets enterprise teams who want Haystack capabilities without self-managing infrastructure. A free tier is available for experimentation."
  },
  {
    question: "Haystack vs LangChain vs LlamaIndex: which to choose?",
    answer: "Haystack is the strongest choice for enterprise NLP pipelines with strict production requirements — robust preprocessing, multiple retrieval strategies, and structured evaluation. LangChain is best for agent-heavy applications and rapid prototyping with diverse LLM integrations. LlamaIndex excels at sophisticated RAG patterns over complex document collections. Haystack's component model is the most explicit and testable of the three, which matters in enterprise settings."
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Haystack: Production-Ready RAG & NLP Pipeline Framework"
  description="Complete Haystack 2.x guide — component-based pipeline architecture, DocumentStore integrations, Retriever-Reader pattern, RAG with LLMs, hybrid retrieval, and comparison with LangChain and LlamaIndex."
  tool="Haystack, RAG pipeline, NLP, document retrieval, deepset, open-source NLP"
  faq={faq}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"Haystack: Production-Ready RAG & NLP Pipeline Framework","url":"https://devplaybook.cc/tools/haystack","description":"Complete Haystack 2.x guide — component pipelines, DocumentStore integrations, RAG, hybrid retrieval, and comparison with LangChain and LlamaIndex."})} />

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Haystack: Production-Ready RAG &amp; NLP Pipeline Framework</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">Haystack is deepset's open-source framework for building production-grade NLP and RAG pipelines. Its component-based architecture lets you compose modular, swappable pipeline stages — document loaders, retrievers, embedders, readers, and LLM generators — into explicit, testable pipelines. The enterprise-grade choice for document Q&amp;A, semantic search, and RAG at scale.</p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Component-based pipelines</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> 10+ DocumentStore integrations</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Hybrid retrieval (BM25 + vector)</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Streaming &amp; async support</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Deepset Cloud managed option</span>
  </div>

  <ToolPageCta />

  <!-- Basic RAG Pipeline -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Building a RAG Pipeline with Haystack 2.x</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Define a pipeline by connecting components explicitly — indexing and querying are separate pipelines in Haystack.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">pip install haystack-ai

from haystack import Document, Pipeline
from haystack.components.embedders import OpenAIDocumentEmbedder, OpenAITextEmbedder
from haystack.components.writers import DocumentWriter
from haystack.components.retrievers.in_memory import InMemoryEmbeddingRetriever
from haystack.components.builders import PromptBuilder
from haystack.components.generators import OpenAIGenerator
from haystack.document_stores.in_memory import InMemoryDocumentStore

# --- INDEXING PIPELINE ---
document_store = InMemoryDocumentStore()

docs = [
    Document(content="Haystack uses a component-based pipeline architecture.", meta=&#123;"source": "docs"&#125;),
    Document(content="RAG combines retrieval with LLM generation for grounded answers.", meta=&#123;"source": "blog"&#125;),
    Document(content="Hybrid search merges BM25 sparse and dense vector retrieval.", meta=&#123;"source": "docs"&#125;),
]

indexing_pipeline = Pipeline()
indexing_pipeline.add_component("embedder",    OpenAIDocumentEmbedder(model="text-embedding-3-small"))
indexing_pipeline.add_component("writer",      DocumentWriter(document_store=document_store))

# Connect component outputs to inputs
indexing_pipeline.connect("embedder.documents", "writer.documents")

# Run indexing
indexing_pipeline.run(&#123;"embedder": &#123;"documents": docs&#125;&#125;)
print(f"Indexed &#123;document_store.count_documents()&#125; documents")</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Query Pipeline -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">RAG Query Pipeline: Retrieve + Generate</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">The query pipeline embeds the user question, retrieves relevant documents, and passes them to an LLM for generation.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">rag_template = """
Answer the question based on the provided documents.
If the answer is not in the documents, say "I don't know."

Documents:
&#123;% for doc in documents %&#125;
  - &#123;&#123; doc.content &#125;&#125;
&#123;% endfor %&#125;

Question: &#123;&#123; question &#125;&#125;
Answer:
"""

# --- QUERY PIPELINE ---
query_pipeline = Pipeline()
query_pipeline.add_component("text_embedder", OpenAITextEmbedder(model="text-embedding-3-small"))
query_pipeline.add_component("retriever",     InMemoryEmbeddingRetriever(document_store=document_store, top_k=3))
query_pipeline.add_component("prompt_builder",PromptBuilder(template=rag_template))
query_pipeline.add_component("llm",           OpenAIGenerator(model="gpt-4o-mini"))

# Wire components together
query_pipeline.connect("text_embedder.embedding",  "retriever.query_embedding")
query_pipeline.connect("retriever.documents",       "prompt_builder.documents")
query_pipeline.connect("prompt_builder.prompt",     "llm.prompt")

# Run query
result = query_pipeline.run(&#123;
    "text_embedder": &#123;"text": "How does Haystack handle retrieval?"&#125;,
    "prompt_builder": &#123;"question": "How does Haystack handle retrieval?"&#125;
&#125;)
print(result["llm"]["replies"][0])</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Hybrid Retrieval -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Hybrid Retrieval: BM25 + Embedding + DocumentJoiner</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Run sparse and dense retrieval in parallel, then merge results with Reciprocal Rank Fusion.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">from haystack.components.retrievers.in_memory import (
    InMemoryBM25Retriever,
    InMemoryEmbeddingRetriever
)
from haystack.components.joiners import DocumentJoiner
from haystack.components.rankers import MetaFieldRanker

hybrid_pipeline = Pipeline()

# Add both retriever types
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("text_embedder",    OpenAITextEmbedder(model="text-embedding-3-small"))
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("bm25_retriever",   InMemoryBM25Retriever(document_store=document_store, top_k=10))
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("embed_retriever",  InMemoryEmbeddingRetriever(document_store=document_store, top_k=10))
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("joiner",           DocumentJoiner(
    join_mode="reciprocal_rank_fusion",   # merge with RRF
    top_k=5
))
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("prompt_builder",   PromptBuilder(template=rag_template))
hybrid_pipeline.add_component("llm",              OpenAIGenerator(model="gpt-4o-mini"))

# Connect: two parallel retrieval branches → joiner → LLM
hybrid_pipeline.connect("text_embedder.embedding",  "embed_retriever.query_embedding")
hybrid_pipeline.connect("bm25_retriever.documents", "joiner.documents")
hybrid_pipeline.connect("embed_retriever.documents","joiner.documents")
hybrid_pipeline.connect("joiner.documents",          "prompt_builder.documents")
hybrid_pipeline.connect("prompt_builder.prompt",     "llm.prompt")

result = hybrid_pipeline.run(&#123;
    "text_embedder":  &#123;"text": "hybrid retrieval BM25 vector"&#125;,
    "bm25_retriever": &#123;"query": "hybrid retrieval BM25 vector"&#125;,
    "prompt_builder": &#123;"question": "What is hybrid retrieval?"&#125;
&#125;)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Table -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Haystack vs LangChain vs LlamaIndex</h2>
